---
import FollowButton from '~/components/atoms/FollowButton.astro';
---

<section>
	<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 overflow-hidden">
		<div class="py-12 md:py-20">
			<div class="py-4 sm:py-6 lg:py-8">
				<div class="flex flex-wrap md:-mx-8">
					<div class="w-full lg:w-1/2 px-0 sm:px-8">
						<div class="mb-12 lg:mb-0 pb-12 lg:pb-0 border-b lg:border-b-0">
							<h2 class="mb-4 text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold font-heading">My Values</h2>

							<div class="mb-8 text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
								<p class="mb-4">
									Start the life with Why. Combine both education and technology. Remote work and asynchronous
									collaboration.
								</p>
								<p>These 3 main values are at the core of what I'm doing for life and work for every single day.</p>
							</div>

							<div>
								<FollowButton />
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="w-full lg:w-1/2 px-0 sm:px-8">
						<ul class="space-y-12">
							<li class="flex md:-mx-4">
								<div class="pr-4 sm:pl-4">
									<span
										class="flex w-16 h-16 mx-auto items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold rounded-full bg-primary-50 text-primary-600"
									>
										1
									</span>
								</div>
								<div class="px-4">
									<h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold font-heading">Start with Why</h3>
									<p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
										<a href="https://simonsinek.com/books/start-with-why">
											Start with Why shows that the leaders who’ve had the greatest influence in the world all think,
											act, and communicate the same way—and it’s the opposite of what everyone else does.</a
										>
									</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex md:-mx-4">
								<div class="pr-4 sm:pl-4">
									<span
										class="flex w-16 h-16 mx-auto items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold rounded-full bg-primary-50 text-primary-600"
									>
										2
									</span>
								</div>
								<div class="px-4">
									<h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold font-heading">Education and Tech</h3>
									<p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
										Educational technology is the combined use of computer hardware, software, and educational theory
										and practice to facilitate learning. When referred to with its abbreviation, edtech, it often refers
										to the industry of companies that create educational technology.
									</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex md:-mx-4">
								<div class="pr-4 sm:pl-4">
									<span
										class="flex w-16 h-16 mx-auto items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold rounded-full bg-primary-50 text-primary-600"
									>
										3</span
									>
								</div>
								<div class="px-4">
									<h3 class="mb-4 text-xl font-semibold font-heading">Remote and Async</h3>
									<p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
										<span>Combine everything from{' '}</span>
										<a href="https://37signals.com/books">
											Remote shows both employers and employees how they can work together, remotely, from any desk, in
											any space, in any place, anytime, anywhere.
										</a>
										<span>,</span>
										<a href="https://twist.com/remote-work-guides/remote-team-communication">
											The art of async: the remote guide to team communication
										</a>
										<span>, and</span>
										<a href="https://blog.doist.com/async-first/">
											Let's move the team toward async-first communication.</a
										>
									</p>
								</div>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
